{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784085177710113003,"compiled_state":{"alias":"courtly-linear-iguana","assignee":"joeoakhart","attestations":{"plan-review":{"algorithm":"HMAC-SHA256","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","head_sha":"bab4f8be3fcf5598d5bd08f4805d9d455eac51ff","key_id":"412fa5372ad877e0","kind":"plan-review","manifest":["plan-review: PASS","ticket: ba33-2310-f6c6-4bd6","material: 87e33a46b532eab6","model: claude-sonnet-4-6","runner: pydantic_ai","blocking: 0","advisory: 2","rebar-version: 0.7.1 (bab4f8be3)","regver: 8952be2f5b88eba7","verified-at-sha:9edb0cdc31d21c9c2ccd1730065225978f258573","dep absent src/rebar/audit/read.py","dep ed13f74604708c18b2839eb14d368316bae98b9bcbfd7fd930c7f0ea3578a783 src/rebar/llm/code_review/sidecar.py","dep fb07969064918fdb4e7c7938ed4cbc620d580fa20707b3e6d8fa70cc1db0847f src/rebar/llm/completion_sidecar.py","dep e34b99d617d90e3cf60ba93bfcdebddde03f53afbb0e09c92b634d60b8286a78 src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py"],"signature":"d38170251fac559f4fab1862e8b39ecf9a69e15e2934058980058f4b9211e9b4","signed_at":1784071116659588000}},"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":0,"unsigned":12},"authorship_ledger":[],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-209_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"90514dff-8b46-4f42-ae53-a1e35fc50ef6","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Epic completion evidence (all 6 child stories closed+signed; Gerrit changes 687/688/692/693/695/698 each LLM-Review+1 & Verified+1):\n- AC 'all child stories closed': 4e19,7c84,e7e0,fde0,46f0,a3db all closed with completion-verifier attestations.\n- AC 'v2 sidecar full four-pass incl pass-4 coaching, all buckets': plan v2 (4e19) — tests/unit/workflow/test_plan_review_workflow.py::test_review_run_emits_lossless_v2_sidecar_via_real_emit_path drives a REAL review -> real emit -> asserts emitted JSON schema=plan_review_result_v2 with per-finding evidence/scenarios/block_threshold/blocking_enabled; code v2 pools blocking/advisory/dropped/indeterminate each w/ verification+pass3+threshold (7c84, test_audit_code_review_v2.py); pass-4 coaching now persisted losslessly {move_id,move_name,subject,finding_refs,coaching} in plan sidecar and verbatim in code sidecar (a3db, test_audit_coaching_fidelity.py).\n- AC 'completion PASS per-criterion record': e7e0 — criteria[] on CompletionVerdict + completion_verifier_pass_v1 sidecar; tests/unit/test_audit_completion_v2.py + tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_completion_gate.py::test_pass_close_persists_criteria_record.\n- AC 'audit read layer full history + relates_to': 46f0 — rebar.audit.read.audit_trail + CLI 'rebar audit show' + MCP audit_trail; tests/unit/test_audit_read.py (aggregate + bare + enumerator + CLI subprocess + MCP).\n- AC 'make lint && typecheck && test pass': all six changes carry Gerrit Verified=+1 (clean-env CI); local make lint/typecheck green.","timestamp":1784084285967114001}],"created_at":1784067113667617001,"deps":[{"link_uuid":"a794239c-cf45-489f-8fe1-8ff31f4eccc0","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"b8e4-e677-9e05-419e"},{"link_uuid":"052460ce-dad4-49d1-b537-259c74de1125","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"62aa-7044-180a-413b"},{"link_uuid":"f01a852a-1cf3-463f-a3f6-effbb1ea8f00","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"a850-1392-55b0-4514"}],"description":"## Context\n\nrebar's three LLM review gates — plan-review, code-review, and completion-verification — each\nproduce a rich internal record, but only a fraction is durably captured today:\n\n- Plan-review and code-review run a shared four-pass kernel (find → verify → decide → coach) and\n  emit a reducer-ignored `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar. The plan-review sidecar drops the pass-1\n  `evidence` and `scenarios` fields; the code-review sidecar persists only the *surfaced* findings\n  (blocking + advisory + coaching) and omits the dropped / indeterminate / overflow buckets. Neither\n  persists the numeric `block_threshold` a finding was judged against — it is resolved from the\n  criteria registry at decision time and then discarded.\n- Completion-verification is single-pass and emits a sidecar ONLY on FAIL; a PASS persists just\n  signed counts, so a successful close leaves no per-criterion audit record.\n- All review sidecars are pruned to the most recent 10 per ticket.\n\nA downstream feature (the ticket audit-trail UI, a separate follow-on epic) needs a COMPLETE,\nself-contained audit record. This epic makes the stored audit data lossless and readable; it builds\nNO UI. The read layer it ships also makes the audit data scriptable via CLI/MCP — valuable on its own.\n\n## Approach rationale\n\nEnrich the existing observability sidecars in place (new schema versions) rather than introduce a\nnew persistence mechanism — the sidecar path is already the durable, reducer-ignored, retained\nrecord every review writes, so extending its payload is the lowest-blast-radius way to capture the\nmissing data. The signed attestation manifest is deliberately left carrying counts only (its\nintegrity contract is out of scope); this epic enriches observability, not the signature.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Every new plan-review and code-review `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar captures the full four-pass record:\n  the complete pass-1 finding list (including previously-dropped fields), the full pass-2\n  verification, the pass-3 determination WITH the resolved numeric threshold, and pass-4 coaching —\n  across ALL buckets, not just surfaced ones.\n- A completion-verification PASS persists a per-criterion audit record (not only counts).\n- Review-sidecar retention is raised so a ticket's review history is deep enough to audit.\n- A documented read API (library + CLI + MCP) returns the full retained audit history for a ticket\n  and resolves a ticket's associated code reviews via the existing `relates_to` links.\n\n## Scope\n\n- IN: sidecar payload enrichment (plan + code), completion PASS-path capture + agent\n  output-contract change, retention-cap change, the audit read layer.\n- OUT: any web UI or rendering (the follow-on epic); asymmetric-key signing; changing what is\n  SIGNED (attestations still carry counts only).\n\n## Compatibility & rollback\n\nSidecar schemas are bumped (`plan_review_result_v2` / `code_review_result_v2` / a completion `_v2`);\nreaders accept BOTH the old `v1` (rendered with the new fields absent) and the new `v2` records, so\npre-existing reviews stay readable and no backfill is required. Each change is inert until it next\nruns; reverting a story restores the prior payload shape with no migration.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All child stories are closed.\n- [ ] After this epic, a freshly-run plan-review and code-review each write a `*_v2` sidecar whose\n      payload contains every pass-1 finding across all buckets with its pass-2 verification, its\n      pass-3 validity/impact/priority/decision/reason, the resolved numeric `block_threshold`, and\n      the pass-4 coaching. Oracle: an integration test runs a review and asserts on the emitted event\n      JSON.\n- [ ] A completion-verification PASS emits a per-criterion audit record. Oracle: a test asserting on\n      the emitted completion event.\n- [ ] The audit read layer returns the full retained history for a ticket and its `relates_to`-linked\n      code reviews. Oracle: an integration test seeding a ticket's histories and asserting the\n      aggregate contains all of them.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py","reason":"epic: plan-review sidecar enrichment"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/code_review/sidecar.py","reason":"epic: code-review sidecar enrichment"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/completion_sidecar.py","reason":"epic: completion PASS capture"},{"path":"src/rebar/audit/read.py","reason":"epic: audit read layer"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["relates_to","62aa-7044-180a-413b"],["relates_to","a850-1392-55b0-4514"],["relates_to","b8e4-e677-9e05-419e"]],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"424aa5cc-f821-499c-ba79-42c6ae0195e0","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"closed","tags":[],"ticket_id":"ba33-2310-f6c6-4bd6","ticket_type":"epic","title":"Audit data enrichment — lossless capture of review passes","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["329ef003-7074-4224-8733-9e976e6690f5"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784085177710113003,"uuid":"cc01847b-cbd0-4fab-9554-1f74fb5fef26"}